text.text:
I think this had to be the most iconic building in Tokyo, and it's well worth the visit.
You'll get some great photos from around the tower, but you really must make the effort to get to the viewing area.
There was a window cleaner cleaning the windows outside during my visit, which was pretty impressive.
You can descend part of the way down on steps outside the building, which is worth doing for some different views of the tower.

text.text: Really enjoyed our Tokyo Tower experience. It’s not as tall as others like the SkyTree but taller isn’t always better. You still get some amazing views here and we only went to the main deck. Timed the visit to watch the sunset and on perfect evening and it was wonderful. Wasn’t too crowded either although people do camp out/ hog window and space at sunset so have to consider getting their early of this is your aim. Also make sure you take the stairs back down! Not many people do it but if you are healthy or don’t mind steps I absolutely recommend it for a different and unique perspective of the tower and views. Very reasonably priced attraction.

text.text:
Tokyo Tower is an absolute must-visit in Tokyo! The panoramic views from the top are breathtaking, offering a stunning perspective of the city skyline, especially at sunset and nighttime when the city lights up beautifully. The tower itself is an iconic symbol of Tokyo, and the atmosphere is both exciting and nostalgic.

The observation decks provide a clear view of famous landmarks, and on clear days, you can even spot Mount Fuji in the distance! The experience is well-organized, with smooth ticketing and helpful staff. There are also great souvenir shops and a variety of attractions within the tower, making it more than just a viewpoint.

Whether you're a first-time visitor or a returning traveler, Tokyo Tower never fails to impress. A perfect blend of history, culture, and incredible views—highly recommended!

text.text: Tokyo Tower is definitely worth a visit! I have been twice and been lucky both times with sunny days! We bought the tickets 1h before our visit via Klook, super easy! There is no need to pay the extra costs to visit the higher level, I would recommend the lower level. It is very crowded and lines, not many areas to sit down and rest. I can not remember how long we stayed but maybe around 1h.

description:
Tokyo Tower, a captivating landmark soaring to a height of 333 meters in the Shibakoen neighborhood of Minato, Tokyo, stands as a testament to architectural ingenuity and offers breathtaking panoramic views.  Its crimson lattice structure, reminiscent of the Eiffel Tower, is instantly recognizable against the backdrop of the sprawling metropolis.  Located at 4-chome 2-8, with a postal code of 105-0011,  the tower is easily accessible and enjoys a prime location, consistently ranking as the #2 attraction out of 63 things to do in Shibakoen, according to TripAdvisor. Boasting a 4.2-star rating on TripAdvisor, based on over 8450 reviews, and a 4.5-star rating on Google based on 84,488 reviews, its popularity is undeniable.

Ascend the tower, and you're greeted with observation decks that provide unparalleled vistas.  On a clear day, the sprawling cityscape unfolds before you, a tapestry of skyscrapers, bustling streets, and tranquil parks.  The iconic structures of Tokyo gleam in the sunlight, while on clear days, even the majestic Mount Fuji can be seen in the distance
